For taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2014, a taxpayer completing a certified rehabilitation to a certified historic structure shall be allowed a credit against the taxes imposed by KRS 141.020 or 141.040 and 141.0401, with the ordering of credits as provided in KRS 141.0205, or KRS 136.505 if:
The certified historic structure is located within the jurisdiction of a consolidated local government or urban-county government;
The amount of qualified rehabilitation expenses exceeds fifteen million dollars ($15,000,000);
The certified historic structure is located within one-half (1/2) mile of a tax increment financing development area which has received at least preliminary approval under KRS 65.490 or 154.30-050; and
Substantial rehabilitation of the certified historic structure begins prior to July 1, 2015.
